"Shell Element — Lateral Load on Wall (Q4)
'Membrane + Plate bending (Bathe Ch.5, Zienkiewicz Ch.14)

"1. Problem Description
'Concrete wall 4m × 3m, thickness 25cm
'Fixed at base, lateral pressure q = 5 kN/m²
'Material: E = 25000 MPa, ν = 0.2

"2. Material Properties
E = 25000MPa
ν = 0.2
t = 25cm

"3. Membrane Constitutive Matrix (in-plane)
#deq D_m = E*t/(1-ν^2)*[1; ν; 0 | ν; 1; 0 | 0; 0; (1-ν)/2]
D_m11 = E*t/(1 - ν^2)
D_m12 = ν*D_m11
D_m33 = D_m11*(1 - ν)/2
D_m = [D_m11; D_m12; 0kN/m | D_m12; D_m11; 0kN/m | 0kN/m; 0kN/m; D_m33]
D_m|[kN/m; kN/m; kN/m | kN/m; kN/m; kN/m | kN/m; kN/m; kN/m]

"4. Bending Constitutive Matrix (out-of-plane)
#deq D_b = E*t^3/(12*(1-ν^2))*[1; ν; 0 | ν; 1; 0 | 0; 0; (1-ν)/2]
D_b11 = E*t^3/(12*(1 - ν^2))
D_b = [D_b11; ν*D_b11; 0kN*m | ν*D_b11; D_b11; 0kN*m | 0kN*m; 0kN*m; D_b11*(1-ν)/2]
D_b|[kN*m; kN*m; kN*m | kN*m; kN*m; kN*m | kN*m; kN*m; kN*m]

"5. Symbolic: Shape Functions and Derivatives
#sym
pdiff((1-a)*(1-b)/4; a)
pdiff((1-a)*(1-b)/4; b)
gradient((1-a)*(1-b)/4; a; b)
hessian((1-a)*(1-b)/4; a; b)
#end sym

"6. Consistent Nodal Forces from Pressure
'q = 5 kN/m² distributed → nodal force = q × tributary area
q = 5kN/m^2
L_x = 4m
L_y = 3m
'Each node gets q × Lx × Ly / 4 (for equal distribution):
F_node = q*L_x*L_y/4
F_node|kN

"7. Lateral Load Vector (4 nodes, out-of-plane DOF)
F = [F_node; F_node; F_node; F_node]

"8. Bending Stiffness (simplified 1 element)
'For thin plate: K_b = ∫∫ Bᵀ·D_b·B dA
'Analytical for rectangular plate:
D_flex = E*t^3/(12*(1-ν^2))
D_flex|kN*m

"9. Maximum Deflection Estimate
'Fixed-free plate under uniform load:
'δ_max ≈ 0.0054 × q × L⁴ / D (for a/b=4/3, 3 edges fixed)
δ_approx = 0.0054*q*L_y^4/D_flex
δ_approx|mm

"10. Symbolic Strain Tensor
#sym strain(u_x*x + u_xy*x*y; v_y*y + v_xy*x*y; x; y)

"11. Symbolic Stress from Strain (Plane Stress)
#sym stress(e_11; e_22; e_12; E; ν)
